Rare Earths
Rare earths are a group of 17 chemical elements used in various technologies and applications.

China
China is a leading producer of rare-earth minerals and has significantly increased its mining and processing capacity.<SEP>China is a major source of rare-earth compounds and metals.<SEP>China's import data was used to estimate rare-earth compound production.

Malaysia
Country with rare-earth mineral production and reserves.<SEP>Malaysia is a source of rare-earth compounds and metals, often derived from concentrates produced elsewhere.

Japan
Japan is a source of rare-earth compounds and metals.

Estonia
Estonia is a source of rare-earth compounds and metals.

United States
The United States is a producer of rare-earth minerals and has significant reserves.<SEP>The United States produces and consumes rare earths, and has a reliance on imports.

Mountain Pass
Mountain Pass, CA is a mine that produces bastn채site, a rare-earth mineral.

Bastn채site
Bastn채site is a rare-earth fluorocarbonate mineral mined in Mountain Pass, CA.

Monazite
A phosphate mineral that contains rare-earth elements and is used for thorium and rare-earth content assessment.<SEP>Monazite is a phosphate mineral containing rare earths, stockpiled in the southeastern United States.

Permanent Magnets
Permanent magnets are a significant end use for rare earths.

Batteries
Batteries are a source for rare earth recycling.

Fluorescent Lamps
Fluorescent lamps are a source for rare earth recycling.

Rare Earth Compounds
Rare earth compounds are chemical combinations of rare earth elements used in a variety of applications.

Rare Earth Metals
Rare earth metals are the pure forms of rare earth elements, used in high-tech applications.

Ferrocerium
Ferrocerium is an alloy containing rare earth elements, used in lighter flints and other applications.

Scandium
Scandium is a rare earth metal with unique properties, used in alloys and specialized applications.

Yttrium
Yttrium is a rare earth metal used in various applications, including ceramics and alloys.

Cerium Oxide
Cerium oxide is a compound used in polishing materials and as a catalyst.

Dysprosium Oxide
Dysprosium oxide is a compound used in permanent magnets and other high-tech applications.

Europium Oxide
Europium oxide is a compound used in phosphors and other specialized applications.

Lanthanum Oxide
Lanthanum oxide is a compound used in optics and other applications.

Mischmetal
Mischmetal is an alloy of rare earth metals used in various applications.

Neodymium Oxide
Neodymium oxide is a compound used in permanent magnets and other high-tech applications.

Terbium Oxide
Terbium oxide is a compound used in permanent magnets and other high-tech applications.

Southeastern United States
The Southeastern United States is a region where monazite, a rare-earth-containing mineral, is stockpiled.

Australia
Australia has 3.3 million tons of Joint Ore Reserves Committee-compliant reserves.<SEP>Australia is a major source of rare-earth mineral concentrates and chemical intermediates.

Nigeria
Nigeria has seen increased rare-earth mineral production.

Thailand
Thailand has increased rare-earth mineral production.

Canada
Canada has significant measured and indicated resources of rare earths.

Russia
Russia holds reserves of rare-earth minerals.

South Africa
South Africa holds reserves of rare-earth minerals.

Vietnam
Vietnam has significant reserves of rare-earth minerals.

Rare-Earth Minerals
Rare-earth minerals are relatively abundant in the Earth's crust but require minable concentrations for extraction.

U.S. Census Bureau
The U.S. Census Bureau is the source of data related to rare-earth compound production.<SEP>The U.S. Census Bureau provides data on rare-earth mineral production.

Argus Media Group
Argus Media Group is the source of data related to non-ferrous markets.<SEP>Argus Media Group provides data related to non-ferrous markets, including rare-earth minerals.

World Mine Production
Refers to the data and trends surrounding global rare-earth mineral mining output.

Government Stockpile
The Government Stockpile holds materials including rare earths for strategic purposes.

Lanthanum
A rare-earth element with increasing production and reserves.

Cerium
A rare-earth element with production and reserves data available.

Bastnaesite
A rare-earth fluorocarbon mineral used for rare-earth content assessment.

Xenotime
A phosphate mineral containing rare-earth elements used for rare-earth content assessment.

Praseodymium
A rare-earth metal produced in California and Utah.

Neodymium
A rare-earth metal produced in California and Utah.

California
California is a state where rare-earth compounds were produced, though data were not included in reported totals.<SEP>US state where rare earth compounds are produced.

Utah
US state where rare earth compounds are produced.<SEP>Utah is a state where rare-earth compounds were produced.

Burma
Country with significant rare-earth mineral production and reserves.

Brazil
Country with rare-earth mineral production and reserves.

India
Country with rare-earth mineral production and reserves.

Madagascar
Country with rare-earth mineral production and reserves.

Tanzania
Country with rare-earth mineral production and reserves.

Zen Innovations
Zen Innovations is the source of data used to estimate production based on import data.

Argus Non-Ferrous Markets
Argus Non-Ferrous Markets is a specific market segment covered by Argus Media Group.

Global Trade Tracker
Global Trade Tracker is a data service provided by Zen Innovations.

Joint Ore Reserves Committee
The Joint Ore Reserves Committee sets standards for reporting mineral reserves.

Domestic Production
Refers to the total production of rare-earth compounds within the United States.

Imports
Refers to the amount of rare-earth compounds brought into the country.

Exports
Refers to the amount of rare-earth compounds shipped out of the country.

Appendix B
Contains definitions related to the data presented in the text.

Appendix C
Contains definitions and information about resource and reserve data sources.

Production Quota
Refers to a set limit on the amount of production.
